cost

    Parameters

Abstract costs

  • costs(data: Serie<IArray> | Alpha): Serie<IArray>

  • Get the costs as a Serie (one cost per point data)

    Example

    costs(data: Serie | Alpha): Serie {
      let d = this.generateData(data)
      // your implementation here
      const e  = normalize(d)
      const ns = normalize(this.measure)
      return square(sub(abs(dot(ns, e)), 1)) // w*(1-d)**2
    }

    See

    JointData

    Parameters

    • data: Serie<IArray> | Alpha

    Returns Serie<IArray>

Abstract generate

  • generate(alpha: Alpha, forExport: boolean): Serie<IArray> | Serie<IArray>[]

  • Generate data according to alpha. Simply stated, given alpha, return the synthetic data (gps, insar, fracture orientation ...) that can be compared to the real measure.

    Example

    class Insar extends Data {
      constructor(private readonly sat: [number,number,number]) {
      }

      costs(data: Serie | Alpha) {
        const compute = this.generateData(data)
        return square(addNumber(negate(abs(div(compute, this.measure))), 1))
      }

      // --------------

      generate(alpha: Alpha): Serie | Serie[] {
        const displ = weightedSum(this.compute, alpha)
        return dot(displ, this.sat)
      }
    }

    Parameters

    • alpha: Alpha
    • forExport: boolean

    Returns Serie<IArray> | Serie<IArray>[]

generateInDataframe

  • generateInDataframe(options: { alpha: Alpha; options?: { [key: string]: any }; prefix: string }): void

  • Genetate synthetic data after the inversion. Derived class must implement this method (see Joint or Congugate)

    Example

    data.generateInDataframe({
         alpha: [1,2,3,4],
         prefix: 'F',
         options: {
             cost: true,
             principalValues: true,
             principalDirections: false,
             normal: false,
             dipAngles: true
         }
    }
